This Questbook provides step-by-step instructions on how to use all the diffrent Mods. Like that you learn quickly and efficiently. The difficulty determines the reward you get for completing a Quest - the more difficult the Quest, the better the reward, of course. 

In my Modpack, most recipes are changed in order to make you use every mod there is to get to your goal. It is of course not only for professional players, but also for rookies. 

§o§d§e§o§b§a§9§d§e§f§k§o§r§o§7§6§5§4§3§7§4§3§oDD&SS has a very special reward system where each player automatically earns Thermal Expansion Coins while questing. Use this Coins to Buy some Stuff in the (Questbook) Shop or use it later to create RF/FE Power.

In woodworking and carpentry, hand saws, are used to cut pieces of wood into different planks or shapes. The hand saw is a bit like a tenon saw, but with one flat, sharp edge.

§1§2- 1x Artisan Handsaw (Any Material)

§1§2- 1x Grip

When used on a Chest (or other similar inventories such as Iron Chests or Storage Drawers), it will pick it up. This chapter provides an introduction on how to use the Blacksmiths Workshop. Above all, the workshop is needed to manufacture armor and tools (Manual Welding). Initially important for hammers and excavators as long as the Toolforge of Tinkers Construct is not available. 

But all armour and some utensils like hoppers must be welded here exclusively (except clay, copper, leather and Avaritia Stuff). You have to organize a burner, fuel gases and other materials. 

There remains a lot of work to be done before we can start to weld something.

Time to craft the workshop itself.

§1§2- 1x Blacksmiths Workshop

The Compost is a block added by Actually Additions. It is used to convert various things. We need this afterwards to make Biomass. 

§1§2- 4x Compost Block

The easiest way to obtain Methane Gas is to put Biomass in a squeezer and jump on top of it! It is not very efficient but at the same time, this process dont need a source of energy. In the longer term, however, its annoying. :D
Use a Redstone Signal to reset the position of the Squeezer.

§a§oHint: The Squeezer can also be used to double ores!

§1§2- 1x Squeezer

The Rudimentary Snare is a tool added by Blood Magic and is the earliest method to collect Demonic Will. Right-click to throw it at a mob. The Demonic Will is an item which can be gathered with the Rudimentary Snare or Sentient Sword from monsters. Every monster can only drop one demonic will with a randomly generated amount of willpower, which is displayed in the inventory. The Demonic Will is required for some recipes in the Hellfire Forge. The size of the will is largely random, but it also roughly correlates to the health of the mob you just killed, so an Enderman will typically generate a more powerful Will than a Spider. 

§2- 1x Demonic Will

The Hellfire Forge is needed to craft recipes requiring Will, which requires Demonic Will or a Tartaric Gem in the right slot that has enough default will to meet the required minimum will. All recipes are shapeless, and ingredients can be in any slot.

This demonic will can be gathered with the Rudimentary Snare or Sentient Sword and is automatically stored into the gem, when the player picks up a Demonic Will. The Petty Tartaric Gem is required for some recipes in the Hellfire Forge and can also be used as source for demonic will for the special attack of the Sentient Sword. 

§2- 1x Petty Tartaric Gem

However, before we start storing anything, put that petty tartaric gem you just made back into the Hellfire Forge in one of the input slots, and put an Iron Sword into another of the input slots. Congratulations, you now have a Sentient Sword. This useful tool will do several things. First off, everything it kills will automatically drop will, no more fooling around with snares. Second off, the more will you have on your person, the more damage it will do. Pretty nice sword.

Lava  -->  1.2 (Value)
Fire   -->  1
Netherrack   -->  0.5
Dirt   -->  0.25
Grass   -->  0.5

Netherwart   --> 1
Beetroot   -->  1
Log   -->  1
